---
import ApiPageHeader from "../components/ApiPageHeader.astro";

const markdown = `# Receipts

A receipt is how this API proves a fact. Clients branch on receipts, not on fluent-looking text.

- Every response names its contract in a \`schema\` tag. Facts land in an append-only journal beside content-addressed artifacts. Read endpoints re-verify stored receipts; tamper fails the whole read.
- Unavailable, unknown, withheld, truncated, and failed are first-class states. The API returns an honest empty list before a fluent guess.
- Passing an audit proves integrity and citation closure, not semantic truth or translation quality.
`;
---

<section class="api-section" aria-labelledby="api-receipts-heading">
  <ApiPageHeader
    title="Receipts"
    headingId="api-receipts-heading"
    description="How this API proves a fact. Clients branch on receipts, not on fluent-looking text."
    markdown={markdown}
  />
  <ul class="api-list">
    <li>
      Every response names its contract in a <code>schema</code> tag. Facts land in an append-only
      journal beside content-addressed artifacts. Read endpoints re-verify stored receipts instead
      of trusting storage; tamper fails the whole read.
    </li>
    <li>
      Unavailable, unknown, withheld, truncated, and failed are first-class states. The API returns
      an honest empty list before a fluent guess.
    </li>
    <li>
      Passing an audit proves integrity and citation closure, not semantic truth or translation
      quality. Semantic scores live on the <a href="/benchmarks/">benchmarks page</a> with their own
      receipts.
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>
